Things happen for a reason, and it is always a good reason regardless of how bad it looks and feels at the moment. I came to this country in 2001 and became a homeless right after. I had nothing, was completely lost and went through a lot since then. Looking back those years, now I know that all those things happened to me for a great reason. Without those experiences I wouldn’t be who I am and wouldn’t have achieved what I have, and wouldn’t have received an offer from Discovery Channel to film my documentary!!
Life will be in your favor if you are faithful and kind. Even the darkest night will end and the sun will rise. Hope my message cheers up many people, especially those who are suffering now! Happy holidays and wishing you a wonderful new year!! And that passion became more powerful when I started giving back! As always I say Be kind for no reason because kindness is free.

I really don't get where this constant negativity from the press about Cristiano comes from ... The Media is just trying to get clicks, and pundits who don't have a career anymore just want to get attention with his big name and try to make him look bad. 

He is soon 38 years old - so what's the surprise that he doesn't score 50 goals a season anymore? Every football fan out there should be happy to have seen him playing world class football for 20 years - I don't think anyone from the new generation will be able to match his numbers again. He will forever be in his own category. 🐐
